parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front air suspension can cause the vehicle to suddenly drop to the ground, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle drops to the ground
the vehicle becomes unstable and shakes
the wheels rub against the body of the car on turns
the vehicle is difficult to drive
and the ESC indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of proper wheel alignment specifications can lead to uneven tire wear, reduced tire life, and potential safety issues due to compromised vehicle handling.
symptoms: Difficulty in finding a service center or authorized dealer to adjust the front tire alignment
inability to properly adjust the front camber and caster adjustments
and uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HECU can cause the brake pedal to travel excessively, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes almost to the floor when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal has a delayed response.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake lights fail to function intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, damage to the vehicle's interior, and failure of various components, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brownish soot within the interior of the vehicle
burnt areas on the driver's side door and seat
melted console
instrument panel failure
failure of electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the trunk can cause a blockage of the rear view, increasing the risk of accidents, and may also lead to property damage or loss.
symptoms: The trunk opens randomly by itself without pressing any button on the dashboard or remote control
blocking the rear view while driving.
